 In production, `DATA_DIR` must be set or the app will throw at startup.
 
+## Features (v2)
+
+- **Character editor** — create/edit characters with class, level, and paragon level
+- **Build editor** — enter a build's gear (per slot), skills, and notes
+  - **Gear editor** — for each of 13 slots: item name/rarity/power, catalog-picked affixes with rolled values, aspect picker
+  - **Skill editor** — add skills picked from the class catalog with ranks; validates against max rank and skill-point budget
+  - Inline validation on affix values, skill ranks, level/paragon bounds
+- **Build detail view** — populated summary of a saved build
+- **Character + build list** — list-detail layout; browse all saves
+- **Cmd-K command palette** — navigate to any character or build, create new, export/import JSON files
+- **File persistence** — one JSON file per character, one per build; Git-friendly diffs
+
+## Data Model
+
+The canonical types live in `lib/types/index.ts`. All subsequent commissions (scoring engine, v3 API import) must use these types. Key entities:
+
+| Entity | Persisted at | Notes |
+|--------|-------------|-------|
+| `Character` | `data/characters/{id}.json` | Class, level, paragon level |
+| `Build` | `data/builds/{id}.json` | Skills, equipped items, paragon boards, playstyle constraints |
+| `EquippedItem` | Embedded in Build | Per-slot, with `RolledAffix[]` and optional `aspectId` |
+
+Builds carry both `equippedItems` (current state) and `targetItems` (theorycrafting targets) — both are available to the scoring engine even when the v2 UI only surfaces current state. `PlaystyleConstraints` and `UptimeValues` fields are persisted even though v2 does not expose UI for them.
+
+## Catalog
+
+Static reference data lives in `lib/catalog/`:
+
+| Module | Contents |
+|--------|---------|
+| `slots.ts` | 13 item slots with cluster groupings and class restrictions |
+| `affixes.ts` | ~75 affixes with min/max ranges, slot eligibility, class restrictions |
+| `aspects.ts` | ~40 legendary aspects with slot eligibility and class restrictions |
+| `skills.ts` | All skills for all 8 classes with category and max rank |
+
+Public API: `affixesForSlot(slotId, class?)`, `validateAffixValue(id, value)`, `skillsForClass(class)`, `validateSkillRank(id, rank)`, `aspectsForSlot(slotId, class?)`. Components import from `@/lib/catalog`, not raw arrays.
+
